paper/Definitions/ contains the MDPI Entropy LaTeX template files
(mdpi.cls, mdpi.bst, journalnames.tex, mdpi_apacite.{sty,bst},
mdpi_chicago.bst, and the MDPI / ORCID / "updates" logos). These are
the property of MDPI AG and are redistributed under MDPI's standard
author terms for use with their journal templates. They are NOT
covered by the CC-BY-4.0 or MIT licenses above; for any reuse outside
the scope of preparing an MDPI submission, refer to MDPI's terms or
download the template directly from https://www.mdpi.com/authors/latex.

paper/main.tex is generated from paper/main.md and reuses MDPI
template macros; the prose and equations within it remain under
CC-BY-4.0 as part of the manuscript. paper/main.pdf is the rendered
manuscript under CC-BY-4.0.

